{"id":2515,"title":"[Simultaneous pancreas-kidney transplantation: patients' perspectives ].","abstract":"Type 1 diabetes mellitus (DM1) is a chronic disease that may affect survival and quality of life in patients due to the development of acute and chronic complications. This review highlights the publications during the past decade on survival and the degree (stabilization/regression) of complications, such as diabetic retinopathy, nephropathy, neuropathy, and macrovascular events in DM1 patients with end-stage renal disease after simultaneous pancreas-kidney transplantation.","date":"2014-12-15","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25509901","annotations":[{"name":"Diabetic retinopathy","weight":0.847996,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetic_retinopathy"},{"name":"Diabetes mellitus","weight":0.840845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus"},{"name":"Diabetes mellitus type 1","weight":0.813282,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus_type_1"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Peripheral neuropathy","weight":0.787886,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peripheral_neuropathy"},{"name":"Retinopathy","weight":0.768171,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Retinopathy"},{"name":"Nephropathy","weight":0.755234,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nephropathy"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.75445,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(medicine)"},{"name":"Organ transplantation","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organ_transplantation"},{"name":"Quality of life","weight":0.720457,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quality_of_l